inn1.comm: high bouncer that climbs well over the batsman ...
good bounce and carry here. It kicked up from short of length outside off, left alone
short in length, outside off, left alone

Salman Butt's comeback doesn't quite last long. Bondy has struck. It was a back-of-length delivery that moved away from the stumps and Butt was almost squared-up as he pushed at it and edged it behind. Fine delivery.
length delivery outside off stump, left alone
around the off stump line, pushed out to the point region
lands back of length around off and moves away ... left alone
fuller in length, again shapes away from the off stump, left alone
leans forward to push it out to cover
lovely movement, again curving away from the off stump, Latif shaped to play at it before he withdrew his bat away
around the off stump, defended on the front foot
short in length again, this one comes back in but starts from middle and hits him high on the thigh pad ...
Bondy!  Full delivery outside off stump, curves away, Younis chased it, going for a flamboyant square drive but only succeeded in edging it behind
outside off stump, left alone
full delivery outside off, Yousuf glides across to play a square-drive but straight to point
length delivery around the off stump line, guided down to third man
Full delivery outside off, Latif seemed to have decided late to  go for it and went too hard into the cover drive but found the gap
He leans forward to drive uppishly but gets it  through covers to pick up the first boundary of the day. Not much foot movement; he just creamed through the line
on the middle, tilting in, Yousuf clips it behind square-leg for a single
moves away from the off stump, left alone
fuller, straighter, on the middle and off, defended back to the bowler
131.1 kmph bouncer and Latif ducks
short in length, around the off stump line, pushed out to short extra cover
very fine shot. It was the outswinger but Latif leans across to cover for the swing and drives it through covers.
on the legs, flicked away
just outside off stump line, covers his off stump before shouldering arms
cuts back in, bounces in, Yousuf is caught on the shuffle and ends up jabbing it away
back of length, on the middle and leg, turned down to fine-leg region
kicks up from short of length, into the ribcage, Latif swivels to swat it to fine-leg region
slower one, full and on the middle and off line, Latif pushes it out to mid-on
moving away from the off stump, around 127 kmph, left alone
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
beaten outsdie off. Around 130 kmph length delivery that just about straightens outside, Yousif was looking for his little dab shot and was beaten
oh lovely outswinger .. around 130 kmph again, fuller this time, lured Yousuf forward into a off drive before it left him late ..
around the off stump, driven straight to short cover
two slips watch on as Yousuf leans across to defend a delivery straightening on the off stump line
fullish, outside off stump, pushed out to cover
around the off stump line, steered towards backward point
143.1 kmph lifting delivery, Latif is late on the pull, beaten for pace and the ball rolls out to wards mid-on
fine delivery. From slightly wide of the crease, he got the ball to shape away late, Latif, feet glued to the ground, just pushes at it and is beaten
this one moves back in and Latif defends to the off side
around the off stump, defended to the off side. Fine over
another one from Southee which moves away from the off stump, left alone
full in length, around the off stump line, Yousuf gets forward to push it to mid-off
on a length, just outside off, dabbed down to third man. He loves playing that shot; uses it a lot to rotate the strike
on a length around the off stump line, squeezed out to third man
fullish, around the off stump line, defended on the front foot
short in length, just outside off stump, punched down to third man
137.3 back-of-length delivery cuts in towards  the off stump, defended on the front foot
full in length, around the off stump line, Yousuf gets forward to ease it to cover
on the middle, Yousuf pushes it to the on side, checks his push-drive, the ball is briefly in air but falls harmless in no-man's land as it rolls to the right of mid-on
banged in short and Latif goes down under
another bouncer, again Latif goes down under
banged in short, around the off stump, tapped down to third man
outswing again, gentle pace, defended to the off side
129.3 kmph delivery swinging away from the off stump, left alone
on the middle, tucked to backward square-leg for a single
short in length, around off, pushed away to backward point
Yousuf breaks free with a charge down the track and lofts it over mid-on.
around the off stump line, guided to point
short in length outside off stump, chopped down to third man
fullish, on the off stump line, squeezed to backward point
full in length around the off stump line, driven to right of short extra cover where a half-stop is made
on the off stump line, jabbed off the inner edge
low full toss, swatted straight to mid-on
length delivery skidding on towards off, jabbed away off the inner edge
back of length delivery around off stump, steered to point
outside off stump line, dabbed away
full in length, around the off stump line, eased out to cover
full delivery outside off stump, driven to the off side
on the off stump line, punched away to sweeper cover
shorter delivery, goes for the pull but it bounces more than what Yousuf anticipated and he takes out the bottom-hand off the handle to adjust as he swats it past square-leg
Dropped by Southee It was a length delivery outside off, Latif flat-batted it, a forehand down the line, back over the left shoulder of Southee who couldn't hold on to the sharp chance
length delivery outside off, pushed to right of point for a single
lovely whip through midwicket. Very typical yousuf. very elegant. Full delivery on the middle and off, flicked away through the on side
leans forward to drive to right of mid-off for a single
drives to the left of short cover where Guptill makes a fine diving half-stop
slightly slower one, fullish, Yousuf mistimes his off drive
drifts down the leg side, short as well, Yousuf wanted to pull but couldn't reach ...
length delivery outside off, Yousuf guides it to third man
length delivery that cuts in, tries to dab it to third man but can't get it past gully
short in length, just outside off, punched to cover
slightly slower, fullish, pushed away to the off side for a quick single
outside off stump line, slightly slower, carves it to short point
back of a length, moves in from outside off, pushed out to sweeper cover
slower one, full and outside off, run down to third man
full and moving down leg, easy decision to call it a wide
length delivery that came in, tucked behind square-leg
full in length around the off stump, defended on the front foot
back of length, coming in, flicked through midwicket
leans forward to drive to left of the bowler
width on offer but Latif mistimes the cut shot
flighted on the stumps, driven back to the bowler
And again.
slows up the pace even further, tosses it on the middle stump line, nudges away to the on side
slightly short in length, cut away to point
on the middle and leg, nudged to the on side
flighted one on the middle, worked to midwicket
leans forward to deflect it to midwicket
Whack. He moved forward to lift it on the up and over mid-off.
fullish, on the middle and leg, Yousuf leans forward to flick it gracefully through midwicket .. Easy on the eye.
just outside off stump, dabbed to gully

Yousuf is run out. It was pushed towards cover point and they run across for the single. Guptill does a superb job, moving to his left , picks up the ball and fires in a direct hit at the non-strikers' end/. Gone!
flighted on the middle stump line, defended to the off
slightly short in length, cut down to deep point
around the off stump, spinning away, edged to the pad
tossed up outside off, pushed out to point
on the middle, turned to midwicket
leans forward to drive it to long-off
around the off stump line, steered towards backward point
length delivery outside off, goes for a big swing across the line but doesn't connect
around the off stump line, guided to point
on the middle, worked through midwicket
banged in short, chopped to the off side
leans forward to push it back to the bowler
flighted around off stump line, driven to covers
tossed up on the leg stump line, beats the defensive poke and hits the pad, going down leg, though
flighted on the middle, eased back to the bowler
shout for lbw but there was an inside edge. It was a loopy delivery on the middle and leg and Umar edged it to his pad
slightly short, cut away to sweeper cover
flighted on the off stump line, defended on the front foot
length delivery just outside off stump, defended to the off side
short in length, turned through to the on side for a single
full in length, outside off, steered straight to backward point
leans forward to turn it to midwicket
short in length, just outside off, worked from there to short midwicket
nice delivery, cut back in from just outside off, runs off the inner half of the bat past square-leg and they run hard to come back for the second run
flighted around off stump line, carved away to right of sweeper cover
on the off and middle stump line, quicker, pushed back to Dan
loopy delivery on the middle, driven inside-out but he can't beat short cover
slows up the pace,. on the off stump line, perhaps just short of length, cut away to sweeper cover
leans forward to push the flighted delivery to the off side
goes right back to clip it off his pads
length delivery that cuts in towards middle, worked past square-leg for a single
leans forward to defend to the on side
just outside off,  nurdled behind square-leg
outside off stump, run down to third man
the slower bouncer, umar shuffles across, waits for it before swatting it past square-leg
just outside off stump, short in length, cut down to third man
on the off stump line, pushed back to the bowler
gives this more flight, on the middle, swept away
what a lovely delivery. It was a tad quicker, landed on a length around the middle stump line, Umar tried to drive but the ball dipped on him before spinning past the blade to hit the off stump.
on the off stump line, driven down to long-off
Slips down the leg side
Full in length, around the off stump line, eased to cover
Length delivery shaping in, punched down to long-on
Good delivery, straightening outside the off stump, Afridi pushes inside the line and is beaten
Leans forward to squeeze it to point
turned past square-leg for a single
quicker one, arm ball, goes right back to defend
Dropped by McCullum. It was sliding down the leg side, tries to swat it away , gets a bottom-edge and McCullum, moving to his left, couldn't hold on
leans forward to defend to the off side
leans forward to work the off break to backward square-leg
moves forward to punch it down to long-on
charges down the track but is beaten in the flight and the ball dips rapidly on him too. Afridi squeezes it back to the bowler
worked around the corner, behind square-leg
quicker one around off stump, edged away to point
good bowling this. Afridi backed away outside leg, looking for the big hit, but Nathan looped across a flighted slow delivery and Afridi lunged out to edge it through vacant slips
floated full outside off, driven to long-off
on the off and middle, straightens, driven down to sweeper cover
flighted on the middle and off, stays on the back foot to punch it to long-on
flatter, quicker, arm-ball, driven back to Dan
aha! flighted really high, above the eye-line, dips on the middle and leg line, tickled around the corner
slightly short in length, punched away to sweeper cover
almost caught and bowled. It perhaps stopped a bit on Afridi who checked his punchy drive but the ball fell short of the bowler
leans forward to sweep it to deep square-leg region
on the middle stump line, chipped to right of long-on
flighted on the off and middle line, chipped in the air but again, well short of the bowler
slips down the leg side, short in length as well, Latif goes right back and across, opens the stance and swings it to deep backward square-leg boundary
stays back to work this one to deep midwicket
flighted on the middle and leg, defended on the leg side
fuller, on the middle, on driven to long-on

It was actually not a bad delivery but Afridi has hit it high over long-on. He charged down the track, Vettori had gone wide of the crease and slowed up the pace, Afridi waited for it even as he was down the track and lifted it up and over
leans forward to tap to the on side for a quick single
full outside off, driven hard but straight to long-off
Thunderous slog sweep. He fetched it from outside off stump and heaved it high over midwicket. Immense fun.
backed away, went for the cut shot but failed to connect with the short of length delivery that skidded outside off
The adrenalin rush has kicked in. WHo can stop Afridi but himself now? He moves down the track and heaves a flighted one over long-off.
stays back to work it past square-leg
moves back and across to tap the off break past square-leg for a single
presses forward before moving outside leg and cuts the off break to sweeper cover
slower one, back of length outside off, tapped close on the off side for a single
short in length, outside off stump, guided to backward point
back of length, around off stump, pushed towards mid-on  and after some hesitation, they scamper across
shuffles across to carve the length ball in the air but well short of sweeper cover
slower one outside off, dragged past square-leg for a single
short in length, heaved away to deep midwicket
here we go. Bondy stars with a slower one, steered to third man
banged in short outsdie off, around 136 kmph, Latif tries to reach out and play the upper cut but doesn't connect

short in length, outside off stump, chopped away to sweeper cover .. but hold on there is some over throws to collect here as the ball is too high for McCullum and it gets past the fielder trying to back-up. Latif reaches his fifty! AFridi rushes across to have a word and taps him on the helmet//
fullish delivery around the middle and leg, chipped over wide midwicket region
length delivery on the off stump line, punched on the up to mid-off
length delivery on the off and middle, pushed out to cover
short in length, outside off, forced away to long-on
fetches it from outside off and swings it wide of deep midwicket region for couple of runs.
moves outside off stump, tries to flick it through the on side but can't beat midwicket
Whaddaplayaaa .. He leaned across, almost going down on his back knee, fetched the ball from well outside off and swept it to deep backward square-leg boundary!
almost yorker length, dug out for a single
full and well outside off, Afridi tries to reach out but can't put bat on ball
Thrash. Fine hit this. It was a length delivery around the off stump line, Afridi knives it on the up and through the line, up and over mid-off. 50 up for Afridi
in the zone outside off, tries to run it down to third man but is beaten
back of length outside off stump, run down to third man
back of length, skids on to the off stump, cut down to backward point
sharp bouncer, too fast and too quick for Latif who is late on the pull and the ball flies to McCullum who doesn't collect it cleanly but recovers quickly to prevent a run
full in length, jabbed out past the bowler
length delivery around off stump, pushed back to the bowler
almost run out. Oram does a superb job to dive to left at mid-off to stop a flat-batted hit and fires in a throw at the non-striker's end. had he hit the stumps, Latif would have been a goner .
clears the front foot and heaves it to long-on
length delivery around the off stump line, punched away to long-off
shuffles across to whip a full delivery from middle stump to deep backward square-leg region
slower one, on a length, on the middle, worked to midwicket
short in length outside off, cut down to sweeper cover
fires across a high bouncer that climbs way over the batsman.. wide
slower one, short in length outside off, run down to left of third man
slightly short in length, pulled away to deep midwicket region

picks the slower one and goes for the big swing to wide long-on region. The bat-face shut a touch at the point of impact and he couldn't time it as he wanted but its' enough for the ball to run away to the boundary
just outside off stump, run down to third man
yorker length on the off, dug out to the bowler
full delivery outside off stump, sliced away in the air towards deep cover where Redmond stops at the last minute, doesn't go for the catch, and stops the ball on the bounce
short in length, outside off, cut down to right of Bond at wide third man
on a length, on the middle, turned away to the on side
around 130 kmph length delivery, not sure whether it stopped on him, chipped away in the air past the non-striker
clears the front foot and heaves it towards long-on
Thrash. Low full toss outside off, dismissed nonchalantly to wide long-on boundary

Oh boy what has happened here. He moved outside off stump, fetched the full toss from well outside off and paddled it straight to short fine-leg fielder. But what an entertaining, yet responsible knock. Lovely mix of fun and work.
back of length, cutting in to the off stump, defended to the off side
in the channel outside off, Akmal is beaten, stabbing inside the line
just outside off stump, pushed out to backward point
banged in short, awkward flat-batted shot to mid-on gets him a single
quickish arm-ball just outside off, cut down to backward point
slower, on the off stump line, pushed out to cover
goes right back to defend a quickish delivery
the arm-ball, flatter and quicker, punched out to long-on
another arm-ball, around off stump, chopped to point region
quicker and flat trajectory - that's the way he has bowled this over - punched to long-off
short in length, around the off stump, punched through point
back of a length outside off, Latif mistimes it back to the bowler
just outside off stump, short in length, cut away to deep backward point
just outside off stump, slower one, guided to third man
short in length outside off stump, punched straight to cover
leans forward to mistime another off drive

cleaned him up with the vicious arm-ball. It skidded on from the leg and middle, Latif was looking for the cut but only managed to stab it to the leg stump. Patient innings, whose value will probably only be known after New Zealand bat, comes to an end. Did he play too slowly? Or did he play a very good knock on this pitch? We just have to wait for the chase to find out.
leans forward to push it to cover
slows up the pace, tosses it around off, edged to short third man
flighted on the middle, pushed out to the bowler
handsome extra-cover drive. It was very full outside off, Akmal lashed it inside-out well to the right of sweeper cover.
on the middle stump line, fullish, pushed down to long-on
full delivery on the stumps, on driven wide of long-on for couple of runs
goes for the yorker, dips as a low full toss, pushed out to cover
full again, driven past the bowler for a single
again just short of the blockhole, driven down to long-on
outside off stump, reaches out to squeeze it past backward point
Awesome hit . Kamran knifed through the line of a length delivery , up and over wide long-off . Flamboyant shot.
Shot. fuller and Akmal crashes it through wide mid-off region.
on the off stump line, pushed out to Vettori at mid-off. Razzaq wants a single, Akmal doesn't
low dipping full toss, driven down to long-on
full pitched around off stump, Razzaq clears the front foot and drives it superbly to the long-off boundary
slightly slower, Razzaq swings it to right of long-on for couple of runs
yorker length on the off stump, dug out to backward point
fires in another full delivery, rolls off the pad to square-leg reigon
wayward delivery down the leg side and McCullum can't reach it
around the off stump, full, square driven to deep point region
full delivery, square drriven to right of backward point where Nathan makes a fine diving stop
No third man and Akmal slices the full delivery over backward point. He opened the bat-face and carved it up and over
sharp yorker, swings in, jabbed out back to the bowler
moves outside leg and edges the big heave to midwicket
low dipping full delivery, driven to long-off
moves outside leg and drives hard but straight to cover
backs away and drives powerfully to long-off
really full one, on the off stump, edges the big hit to midwicket
full delivery, driven down to long-off for a single
full and outside off, goes for the big drive, squeezes it out to the keeper
down the leg side and it rolls past the diving keeper
Akmal loves his square drives and keeps going for it. He sliced this one high over deep backward point
Thrash. Superb hit. He moved outside leg, went down on his back knee and square drove it to the point boundary.
dropped by Styris at third man region. Akmal sliced another length delivery over backward point. He didn't quite connect well and Styris rushed back but fumbled the catch
backs away to drive to the off side
full delivery, driven down to long-on
low dipping full toss, driven to long-off
another full toss and this time Akmal paddles it past the short fine-leg fielder. Pakistan are charging on in style
goes for another paddle shot and gets it to deep backward square-leg region
low full toss outside off, driven to deep cover and he has reached his 50. What a thrilling cameo.
Walloped over long-off. It was the full pitched delivery just outside off and Razzaq has crashed it for a six
thunderous hit. Another full delivery and Razzaq smoked it really hard and just over the leaping long-off fielder. It was flat brutal hit
goes for the slower one, slips in a full toss above the waist- high ( so no ball but not a free hit ) swung away to deep midwicket
length delivery drifting down the leg side, Razaq tries to swat-pull it away but it runs off the pads ,past the diving McCullum

fullish delivery, in the slot, Razzaq goes for the big hit down the ground but skies it straight up towards cover. More elevation than distance. Styris came under the ball, juggled it a bit before holding on. Fine cameo from Razzaq.
Umar Gul is run out. It was pushed to cover and Akmal called him for a single but Gul couldn't get across in time to beat the throw
What a shot. Stunning hit. He backed away outside leg, went down on his back knee and flayed the full delivery over cover boundary. Catch it on the youtube soon
goes for the repeat of the shot but doesn't connect this time
short of length delivery, bounces to catch the edge and a simple catch to Baz
Ouch. A fiery bouncer, Ajmal is late on the pull and is hit on the helmet and they scamper across for a single. Styris with the throw and had he hit Ajmal would have been run out.
full delivery, drilled to long-off but he doesn't take the single as he wants the strike
its a full delivery outside off, Akmal moves outside leg stump and reaches out to slash it to deep point region
Some one fetch that. Full delivery on the off stump line, Akmal clears the front leg and goes down town. The ball flies over the straight boundary.
really full delivery outside off, squeezed out to backward point

inn2.comm: short in length, around the off stump line, defended back to the bowler
fuller, just outside off, left alone
short in length, on the leg stump line, McCullum goes for the pull but doesn't connect and the ball bounds off his body to fine-leg region
bouncing delivery angling across McCullum who tries to get back and across but is beaten for pace
lovely delivery, curving in from around the off stump, McCullum stabs it off the inner edge to back thigh
walks down the track, gets a short-of-length delivery, guided out to backward point
really full delivery, just outside off, it goes under the bat, under the drive, and to the keeper
short in length, straightening outside off stump, left alone
short in length, in the zone outside off, left alone
beaten outside off. This one curves away late, Redmond has a waft but ...
And again. It straightens from short of length and Redmond ends up pushing inside the line
on the off stump line, jabbed off the inner edge. Fine probing over
length delivery straightening on the stumps, McCullum is clueless and is rapped high on the pad ..
fuller, around the off stump, curves in, Baz goes for a cover drive but is beaten by the inward movement and edges it to the on side
full inswinging delivery around off, driven to left of mid-off
walks across, tries to short-arm pull a short-of-length delviery but is beaten for pace again. Aamer gets the ball to skid on really quick and that skiddy pace is upsetting Mccullum's rhythm
this one angles away from Redmond who has a flash at it but misses
lovely delivery, inswinger on the middle stump line, almost lbw but Redmond just about gets the bat in line and gets the inner edge
Baz breaks free with a cover drive. So far he was looking for the big shots but this time it was just the conventional cover drive. Nay . it was just a firm push and the ball raced away
on the middle stump line, pushed out towards mid-off. Free hit coming up
Crash. Full pitched delivery around off stump and McCullum thrashes it high towards long-off .. one bounce and over the boundary
short in length, slightly slower, gets past the attempted cut and it bounces once before it reached the keeper
walks down the track, Gul gets the ball to cut back in, moves past the prod and bounces into the body
slower one, short in length, punched to cover
around the off stump line, steered to point
walks couple of steps, Aamer shortens the length, steered to backward point
outside off stump, skidding across, runs off the inner edge to fine-leg region
fine delivery, cutting back in with bounce, moves past the defensive prod and strikes him high ..
fuller, around off stump, squeezed out to backward point
loud shout for lbw but it pitched outside leg and was high as well. It moved in towards middle, bouncing away, the batsman doesn't offer a shot and is hit on the pad ..
what a fine spell this has been from the Aamer. The batsmen are in all sorts of trouble. This one was full and outside off, curving in late, another inside edge
dropped by Butt at first slip. It was the full delivery outside off, McCullum edged the intended cover drive and Butt lunged low to his right but couldn't hold on
drops this shorter and McCullum pulls it away to the square-leg boundary
Crashed. Short in length and outside off stump, McCullum stays back to square-cut it really hard through point
slightly slower one, guided to third man
superb extra cover drive. It was fullish and outside off, Redmond eased forward to caress it through the off-side field
length delivery straightens around off, pushed out to cover
walks down the track and turns the back-of-length delivery though midwicket
banged in short, sways away from the line
leans forward to push to cover
kicked up from short of length and moves away, beaten as he tries to run it down to third man
and what a spell this has been ... this one moves in with bounce to crash into the thigh pad
And again. Aamer is the maan. he has been too good for these batsmen
leans forward to push to cover
short in length, outside off, walks out to push to cover
bouncing delivery on the off stump line, late on the pull and ends up jabbing it to the leg side
And there we go. The first wicket has  fallen. It was slightly short in length straightening outside off, McCullum tried to fetch it from there with a pull shot but dragged the ball on to the stumps.
lands on a length outside off and straightens, left alone
almost takes out the middle stump with a yorker, just about dug out in time
on the middle and leg, full in length, tucked past square-leg
around the off stump line, leans forward to defend
lands on a length outside off and veers away further, left alone
full in length, outside off, left alone
leans forward to push it wide of mid-on
leans forward to defend
full delivery on the middle, eased to mid-on

Another fatal inside edge. It was a short of length delivery that skids on straight, Guptill was looking to defend but is late in getting the bat down, pushes it outside the line and it collides with the inside  and ... timber!
full in length outside off stump, stabbed out to the off side
leans forward to drive to cover
on a length around off stump, driven hard back down the track and Umar Gul tries to stop it from front of his face but ricochets it to his groin. Ouch!
fires it full outside off and he crashes it straight to backward point
fullish in length outside off and he drives straight to cover point

the thickest of edges and he's gone! He fires it in outside off and angles it across the right-hander, Taylor chases it and shapes to carve it over extra cover but he gets a thick edge which thuds into Kamran's gloves
he bowls it full outside off and he drives firmly but mistimes it a bit but finds the gap at cover
gets beside the line and steers him down to point, extra bounce this time
angles it across the right-hander and he shoulders arms
low full toss and the ball travels off the toe of the bat and rolls down to second slip
hits a good length outside off and he safely shoulders arms
hits a good length just outside off and he softly taps it back to the bowler
stays back at the crease and he taps it to the off side
delivers from slightly wide of the crease and he gets beside the line and steers him to cover
lands it outside off and he steers him down to point
straightens after pitching and he safely lets it go to the keeper. that's a maiden
low full toss, punched away sweetly through covers
short in length outside , punched away to backward point
around the off stump line, pushed out to the off side
on the off stump line, squeezed off the outer edge to third man
tip and run, tapped close on the off side and off they go
short in length, outside off, punched away to short extra cover
back of length around off stump, pushed out to cover
turns from the off stump, defended to point
flighted around off stump, driven to mid-off
slower through the air, on the middle, driven to long-on
around the off stump line, driven to sweeper cover
skids in , jabbed off the inner edge to the pad
floated outside off and Redmond lifts it over mid-off
Styris fan club would be disappointed. It was short in length and Styris pulled it high towards deep square-leg where Farhat (substitute) rushes to his left to pluck off a good catch
on the legs, flicked away to deep square-leg and Aamer comes across to pick it up
leans well forward to defend to cover
fullish, around off stump, eased to Afridi at cover
around the off stump line, chopped down to third man
turned past square-leg

leans forward to clip it o right of Umar akmal at short midwicket who makes a super diving stop but doesn't recover quickly and doesn't grab the ball in time .. had he done so Vettori might have been run out
leans forward to defend to off side
around the off stump, steered through point
googly outside off, Vettori is beaten on the forward prod
leans forward to work it past square-leg
flighted loopy delivery outside off, driven to sweeper cover
outside off stump, pushed out to covers for a single
